# AOR Common Taxonomy

- `@aor/types`: shared transport schemas and exported types consumed by frontend and backend.
- `@aor/ports`: shared contracts or tokens used across package boundaries.
- `@aor/domain`: pure shared domain logic with no framework, database, or HTTP concerns.
- `@aor/adapters`: technical implementations of shared ports.
- `@aor/utils`: pure stateless helpers.
- `@aor/logger`: logging abstractions and logger implementations.

## Placement Rules

- Keep app-specific admin, participant, or Nest wiring out of `aor-common` unless the code is genuinely shared.
- Backend feature-specific use case symbols should stay in backend presentation modules such as `applications/backend/src/presentation/**/**.tokens.ts`.
- Do not move generic helpers into `@aor/adapters` or `@aor/logger` just because they are reused once; use `@aor/utils` when the code is pure.
